           SPELL=mgetty
         VERSION=1.1.28
            DATE=Jan10
          SOURCE=$SPELL$VERSION-$DATE.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-$VERSION
   SOURCE_URL[0]=ftp://alpha.greenie.net/pub/$SPELL/source/1.1/$SOURCE
        WEB_SITE=http://alpha.greenie.net/$SPELL
         ARCHIVE="off"
         ENTERED=20020813
         UPDATED=20020813
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
          MD5[0]=dc5de3eb1cf75f37e60fb94e321cdcd7
      MAINTAINER=shdwdrgn@sourpuss.net
           SHORT="mgetty+sendfax is a fax send and receive solution for unix and linux."
cat << EOF

mgetty allows you to make optimum use of your modem or fax modem in a unix
environment.  mgetty handles incoming calls without interfering with outgoing
calls.  If the modem can do fax class 2 or 2.0, mgetty can also receive faxes.

sendfax is a standalone backend program to send fax files.

Note:  mgetty will not resurrect correctly, and the ARCHIVE="off" function is
       not currently working.  In order to get mgetty to re-install after an
       initial install, you must run 'cast -r -c mgetty'.

EOF
